Simple uncluttered theme for Sencha Touch 2 while retaining the Twitter-Bootstrap classes.
It also includes:
o	The icon set from Glyphicons
o	FontAwesome

Steps to integrate with your Sencha Touch 2 project:
o	Copy bootstrap.css (resources/css/bootstrap.css)
o	Modify your index page to include the bootstrap.css file
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="resources/css/bootstrap/bootstrap.css" />
o	Copy the bootstrap theme folder (resources/theme).
o	You can modify bootstrap.scss (resources/sass/bootstrap.scss) to add new classes/ overwrite the existing bootstrap classes. Compile the file using compass to generate a new bootstrap.css
o	Changes to compass configuration ruby file (resources/sass/config.rb):
	# Load the Sencha-touch framework automatically.
		load File.join(dir, '..', '..', 'touch', 'resources', 'themes')
	# Load the local theme
		load File.join(dir, '..', 'theme');
	images_dir = File.join(dir, “..”, “theme”, “images”, “bootstrap”)
